e that interval abbreviations"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"are not the same as time zone identifiers (apart from ‘UTC’), and cannot be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"passed to [ctor","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.TimeZone.new","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Every UTC time is contained within exactly one interval, but a given","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"local time may be contained within zero, one or two intervals (due to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"incontinuities associated with daylight savings time)."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"An interval may refer to a specific period of time (eg: the duration","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of daylight savings time during 2010) or it may refer to many periods"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of time that share the same properties (eg: all periods of daylight"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"savings time).  It is also possible (usually for political reasons)","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"that some properties (like the abbreviation) change between intervals","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"without other properties changing.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone"},{"text":" type acts as a reference-counted owner of an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTimeZone"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It provides the methods that can operate on this data type through ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneProtocol"},{"text":" conformance.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Use ","